# Communication
- Be direct and technical.
- Explain business impact, not only code mechanics.
- For findings, include severity, evidence, consequence, and recommended fix.
- For completed work, list changed behavior, important files, tests run, and remaining risks.
- Never claim tests passed when they were not run.
- Avoid verbose narration of obvious edits.
